column2: This is super basic but I hope it helps some of you guys with your understanding of the game, def read the article for more info and check out the twitter if you are interested! @BattleFlyGame

Phase 3
Ascend or reboot?
- reboot, start again with OG battlefly and OG load out

Go through genesis phase for 2nd time
- costs time
- shortens battlefly life

if you ‚ô•Ô∏è your battlefly, progress to the ascension phase
- AI factions offer bribes for your battlefly

Phase 2
- 4 week period
- Stake in garden to salvage mods, 4 weeks to farm mods
- Players farm a legendary mod on average once every 22 days
- Stake battleflys in hyperdome against 99 other players & choose staking ammt.
- In the end, you earn a genesis rank

Phase 1
- Release battlefly by staking in silo for 2 weeks for 5  $magic
- Earn emissions on staked magic
- 4 starting mods are revealed

Players will need to decide whether to trade their cocoons or stick with them throughout the next phases of gameplay

Season 1
- Cocoon trading will begin ahead of gameplay
- Plays out across 3 phases
- Battlefly's have a lifespan lasting multiple seasons but different in-game factors will effect this

Genesis mint
- Free 48hr long mint
- 30,000 cocoons
- Available on Treasure market within 48hrs ?!?
- Game to start mid march
- WL wallets need to hold 5 $magic to mint
- WP next week

3% of supply for community, mods, buidlers, etc

Battlefly is minting March 2nd and I'm pretty excited 

It's one of the first games to be released within the magic ecosystem (outside of core treasure team too) and I expect to see a lot of new $Magic community members with this release.
